
# AWS Command Line Interface (CLI)

For the Command Line Interface (CLI) to work, we need to configure it to work using Access Keys.

1. Download AWS CLI in your system.
2. Go to the user section in management console in AWS and under Users > Security Credentials > Create an Access Key
3. Choose Command Line Interface.
4. Now, you have your Access Key and Secret Key ready.
5. Fire up the AWS CLI in your system and type in the command `aws configure`.
6. Enter the Access Key ID, Secret Key, Default Region Name,Default output format.
7. Check the working of the AWS CLI using any command such as `aws iam list-users`.


